ab to me\n1. On laptop, open Chrome.\n2. Install/enable the **OpenClaw Browser Relay** extension.\n3. Open the page you want me to work on.\n4. Click the OpenClaw Relay toolbar icon on that tab until the badge shows **ON**.\n5. Come back here and say: **“tab attached”**.\n\nOnce you say that, I can control that tab directly and do the work.\n\n---\n\n## Important reality check\n- I **cannot silently take over your whole laptop/screen** with admin PowerShell.\n- I can control what you explicitly connect (attached browser tab, or a paired node device with consent).\n\n---\n\nIf you want full device-level pairing after this (beyond browser tab), I’ll walk you through that next too.","textSignature":"msg_09754d96df40a1610169a219fe27588191baae5472a1e31943"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.3-codex","usage":{"input":205,"output":576,"cacheRead":16128,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":16909,"cost":{"input":0.00035875,"output":0.008064,"cacheRead":0.0028224,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.011245149999999999}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772231159609}}
