lanning robust gateway connection setup**\"}]}"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Got it — **token mismatch** usually means the extension is pointed at a different OpenClaw profile/gateway than the one I’m on.\n\nDo this exact reset:\n\n1. On the machine running OpenClaw, run:\n   ```powershell\n   openclaw status\n   ```\n   Confirm gateway is this one: `ws://127.0.0.1:18789` (or your current shown URL).\n\n2. In Chrome extension settings, clear old connection/token, then re-enter:\n   - **Gateway URL** = the one from `openclaw status`\n   - **Token** = current token from your active Control UI session (copy fresh)\n\n3. Make sure you are **not mixing dev profile**:\n   - Don’t use `--dev` on one side and normal profile on the other.\n\n4. Restart gateway once:\n   ```powershell\n   openclaw gateway restart\n   ```\n\n5. Re-open Chrome tab, click Relay icon to **ON**.\n\n---\n\nIf you want, paste the exact extension fields you’re using (URL + whether `--dev` was used), and I’ll pinpoint the mismatch in one shot.","textSignature":"msg_09754d96df40a1610169a21a272e1c8191abc2d50d23a0dc96"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.3-codex","usage":{"input":834,"output":693,"cacheRead":16640,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":18167,"cost":{"input":0.0014595,"output":0.009702,"cacheRead":0.0029119999999999997,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.014073500000000001}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772231198362}}
