y_to_current]] Yep — that prompt is normal. It wants the **gateway token from this main machine**.\n\nDo this:\n\n1. On the **main machine** (where I’m running), open:\n   - `http://127.0.0.1:18789/` (Control UI)\n\n2. In Control UI, go to Gateway/Connection settings and **copy the token**.\n\n3. On the laptop extension popup, paste:\n   - **Gateway URL:** `ws://192.168.1.144:18789`  \n     (use LAN IP, not 127.0.0.1, since laptop is a different device)\n   - **Token:** paste the copied token exactly\n\n4. Save, then toggle the tab relay **ON**.\n\n5. Tell me: **“tab attached”**.\n\nIf it still fails, send me the exact error text and I’ll fix the next blocker immediately.","textSignature":"msg_09754d96df40a1610169a21b1dc66c8191818035cf894d4cec"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.3-codex","usage":{"input":55012,"output":309,"cacheRead":1536,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":56857,"cost":{"input":0.096271,"output":0.004326,"cacheRead":0.0002688,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.10086579999999999}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772231449815}}
