con (bottom-right).\n2. Connect to the **same Wi‑Fi name** your main machine uses.\n3. Open Command Prompt and run:\n   ```cmd\n   ipconfig\n   ```\n4. Look at `IPv4 Address`.\n\nYou want laptop IP to look like `192.168.1.xxx` (same first 3 chunks as mine `192.168.1.144`).\n\n---\n\n### If laptop is on different network\n- Switch laptop Wi‑Fi to the same router network.\n- Turn off VPN/hotspot on laptop temporarily.\n\n---\n\n### Then retry extension\n- URL: `ws://192.168.1.144:18789`\n- Token: your token\n- Relay ON on a Google tab\n\nIf you want, paste your laptop `ipconfig` output and I’ll tell you immediately if it’s on the wrong network.","textSignature":"msg_09754d96df40a1610169a2212a03e08191af5da27ba20abba6"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.3-codex","usage":{"input":527,"output":296,"cacheRead":61184,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":62007,"cost":{"input":0.00092225,"output":0.004144,"cacheRead":0.0107072,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01577345}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772232998849}}
